Head: with ca. 46 ocelli (
Fig. 73
), arranged in 6 rows (3: 6: 7: 10: 8: 11).

Distribution and habitat:
This species is only known from The Cascades at Bluff Knoll and the south face of Pyungoorup Peak in 
Stirling
Range National Park (
Fig. 5
). The surrounding vegetation is dominated by sparsely growing jarrah (

Eucalyptus marginata

) and marri (

Corymbia calophylla

).
